<textarea name="message" rows="12" cols="50" wrap="virtual" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Taikuri Zauberei:
[QB]I really wish someone would do a proper study of charisma.  I have the FEELING that once you get to lev 60, a higher charisma doesnt help you, because the stuff you are mezzing is already at the lowest resist rate due to your level.  So if someone at lev 60 is testing charisma...they may have completely different results from, say, a lev 45 doing it.

I have never seen a valid study which proved one way or the other the effects of charisma on mezzing or charming.

All the studies I have seen fail to take into account varying mob levels, or varying enchanter levels, or some other variable.

I have a sneaking suspicion that charisma has more effect than many think.  Last night with my charisma pumped up near 200, i was able to mezz a lev 55 mob 5 times in a row with no resists.  I am lev 47.

Later on I switched out of my charisma gear, and had an awful amount of trouble mezzing drolvargs and drachnids in DL that were blue to me.

I will try mezzing the lev 55 mobs again tonight without my cha gear and see how that works.

-Taik

I am positive that at some level, the effect of charisma becomes negligable..but I have the sneaking suspicion that it means quite a bit to the growing enchie.

I seriously hope i can prove myself wrong so i can stop carrying cha gear around and go for hp gear.[/QB][/QUOTE]
</textarea>
